question.title: Maven hangs while running test case Eclipselink & hsqldb

node.contents: Using jps and jstack I can get to the offending waiting thread but don't know how to troubleshoot it or what is causing it. See below the Maven dependencies and the jstack result and the waiting thread with tid=0x000000000022c000. Analysing further it seems an issue between Eclipselink and hsqldb for the chosen versions. I got this issue as result of upgrading those two libraries since it used to work perfectly for versions 2.0.1 and 1.8.0.10 of Eclipselink and hsqldb respectively.

node.contents: MVCC means Multiversion Concurrency Control. It avoids locking whole database tables when a thread modifies a row. It allows other threads to read the whole table and to modify different rows, even before the first thread has committed.

astNode.text: MVCC means Multiversion Concurrency Control. It avoids locking whole database tables when a thread modifies a row. It allows other threads to read the whole table and to modify different rows, even before the first thread has committed.

node.contents: This is also equivalent to SET DATABASE TRANSACTION CONTROL MVCC More info: http://hsqldb.org/doc/2.0/guide/sessions-chapt.html#snc_tx_tx_cc

astNode.text: This is also equivalent to SET DATABASE TRANSACTION CONTROL MVCC More info: http://hsqldb.org/doc/2.0/guide/sessions-chapt.html#snc_tx_tx_cc

node.contents: It does indeed look like a hsqldb issue. Following directions from here the solution was to append the following to the connection-url ;hsqldb.tx=mvcc whatever that means :/
